  "text": "Cytotoxicity was determined by MTT assay performed a published previously. [CITATION_1] To illustrate, cells were plated at 8×10 3 cells per well into 96-well plates and allowed to attach overnight. Then, the cells were treated with various concentrations of UA (0, 5, 6.25, 10, 12.5, 20, 40, 50ug/ml) for 48h in a minimum of three replicate wells. Each well was then added 20ul MTT, prepared by mixing 5mg MTT with 1ml normal saline, and incubated for an additional 4h. Medium in each well was replaced with 150ul DMSO. Absorbance was determined with a microplate reader (BIP-RAD) at 490nm. The blank control wells were used for zeroing absorbance. The inhibition rate (IR%) was calculated using the background-corrected absorbance by the following equation:",
